    <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample">
      <div class="accordion-body">
        <p>
          Exploring unknown streets can be an exciting adventure, but it's important to prioritize your safety. When navigating unfamiliar areas, consider the following safety precautions:
          Stay alert and be aware of your surroundings at all times. Pay attention to the people around you and any potential risks or hazards.
          <br>
          <br>
          Plan your route in advance and use reliable maps or GPS navigation to minimize the chances of getting lost.
          Avoid walking alone at night in unfamiliar or poorly lit areas. If you must venture out after dark, try to stick to well-populated and well-lit streets.
          Trust your instincts and avoid any situation or individual that makes you feel uncomfortable or uneasy. If something doesn't feel right, it's better to err on the side of caution.
          <br>
          <br>
          Keep your valuables secure and out of sight. Avoid displaying expensive jewelry, gadgets, or large amounts of cash that might attract unwanted attention.
          Be cautious when accepting help or directions from strangers. It's always best to seek assistance from official sources such as police stations, tourist information centers, or reputable establishments.
          Familiarize yourself with local emergency contact numbers and have them readily accessible in case of any unforeseen circumstances.
          <br>
          <br>
          Remember, personal safety should always be your top priority when exploring unknown streets. By staying vigilant, using common sense, and taking necessary precautions, you can have a safe and enjoyable experience discovering new places.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
