          <br>
          <br>
          Dress appropriately: Respect the local customs and dress modestly, especially in conservative areas. This can help you blend in and reduce unwanted attention.
          Stay aware of your surroundings: Be alert and mindful of your surroundings, especially in unfamiliar areas. Trust your instincts and avoid risky situations.
          <br>
          <br>
          Secure your belongings: Keep your valuables secure, use a money belt or hidden pouch, and be cautious of pickpockets. Avoid displaying expensive jewelry or flashy items that may attract unwanted attention.
          Use reliable transportation: Opt for reputable transportation options, such as licensed taxis or rideshare services. Avoid traveling alone late at night, and if possible, use well-lit and busy routes.
          <br>
          <br>
